Additional Instructions
Write clean, well‑commented code.

Use environment variables for the Gemini API key.

Include a sample dataset (e.g., sample_sales.csv) with at least 100 rows and columns: date, region, product_category, revenue, units_sold, quarter.

For the LLM prompt, design a system prompt that instructs Gemini to output JSON containing:

sql_query (if using a database) or data_operation (if using pandas)

chart_type (e.g., "line", "bar", "pie", "table")

title for the chart

x_axis, y_axis fields

Any filters applied

Parse this JSON on the backend, execute the query against the data, and return both the data and the chart configuration to the frontend.

On the frontend, dynamically render charts based on the configuration.